constructor()
ngOnChanges() - when data pass parent to child via @Input decorator. only work for primitive data types. it will hold one parameter (changes:Simplechnages)
ngOnInit()
ngDoCheck() - whenever you want to detect changes from a variable decorated by @Input.it track the change detection with non premitive data types
ngAfterContentInit() - @ContentChild()
ngAfterContentChecked()
ngAfterViewInit() - when you want to call a lifecycle hook after all child components have been initialized and checked. @viewChild, @viewChildren
ngAfterViewChecked()
ngOnDestroy()

difference between ngOnChanges() and ngDoCheck()
